 ## Storage Layout
 
+Global (per-user) files follow the XDG base-directory layout, resolved by
+`Hive::Paths` (see [wiki/modules/paths.md](../wiki/modules/paths.md)):
+
+```text
+~/.config/hive/config.yml        # project registry + provider/model (global)
+~/.local/state/hive/             # daemon pid, logs/ (runtime/tracking state)
+~/.local/share/hive/<version>/   # install.sh-managed self-contained app dir
+~/.cache/hive/                   # regenerable cache
+~/.local/bin/hive (or hv)        # launcher symlink
+```
+
+Setting `HIVE_HOME` collapses all of these under one directory (the pre-XDG
+single-home layout), and a pre-existing `~/Dev/hive` install is honoured for
+back-compat. Homebrew/AUR installs keep their files under the package
+prefix; only `install.sh` uses `~/.local/share/hive`.
+
 `hive init .` creates the per-project storage tree:
 
 ```text
