 These recipes are meant to be copied into real project work. They use the current eight-stage workflow.
 
+## Install & Upgrade
+
+Install through one channel (see [install.md](../install.md) for the full agent-driven prompt and per-host channel selection):
+
+```bash
+brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive                                                   # macOS / Linuxbrew
+yay -S hive-bin                                                                        # Arch (AUR)
+curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh | bash   # fallback
+```
+
+`hive update` upgrades through whichever channel you installed with — it never swaps files in place, it drives the native updater (`brew upgrade`, `yay -Syu hive-bin`, or a re-run of `install.sh`). Preview without running via `--dry-run`:
+
+```bash
+hive update            # runs brew/install.sh; prints the command for AUR / dev checkouts
+hive update --dry-run  # print the command only
+hive update --json     # hive-update.v1 envelope
+```
+
+`hive uninstall` stops and deregisters the daemon service, removes install.sh-managed files (or prints `brew uninstall` / `pacman -R hive-bin` for package-managed installs), and **always preserves** your work under `~/.local/state/hive` and every project's `.hive-state`:
+
+```bash
+hive uninstall           # interactive; prompts before dropping the global registry config
+hive uninstall --purge   # non-interactive; drops global config too, still preserves work
+```
+
+Agent skills are removed through your agent's marketplace (e.g. `claude plugin marketplace remove hive`), not by `hive uninstall`.
+
 ## Xbookmark End-To-End
 
 The xbookmark dogfood task started from this idea (typo `conenct` preserved from the original):
