+# Install Hive (agent prompt)
+
+Paste this whole block into any coding agent (Claude Code, Codex, Pi, or another
+CLI that can read terminal output and run shell commands). The agent will detect
+your OS, pick the best install channel, install the `hive` binary, verify it, and
+then offer the follow-up steps. It has explicit stop-conditions so it halts and
+reports instead of guessing or mutating your machine silently.
+
+```text
+Install the `hive` CLI (github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive, v0.1.0) the best way for
+this host. Follow the numbered plan and honour every stop-condition. Do NOT edit
+my shell rc files (~/.bashrc, ~/.zshrc, ~/.profile, fish config, etc.) silently —
+if a step would change PATH, tell me the exact line and let me apply it.
+
+Plan:
+
+1. DETECT OS + ARCH.
+   Run `uname -s` and `uname -m`. Record the OS (Darwin = macOS, Linux = Linux)
+   and the architecture (arm64/aarch64 vs x86_64). Report what you found before
+   choosing a channel.
+
+2. CHOOSE THE INSTALL CHANNEL (first matching branch wins).
+   State out loud which branch you are taking and why.
+     a. macOS (Darwin) AND `brew` is on PATH:
+          brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive
+     b. Arch Linux (an `/etc/arch-release` file exists OR `pacman` is on PATH)
+        AND an AUR helper `yay` is on PATH:
+          yay -S hive-bin
+     c. Linux with Homebrew/Linuxbrew (`brew` is on PATH, typically
+        /home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin/brew):
+          brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive
+     d. Otherwise (any other Linux, or a host with none of the above):
+          curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/download/v0.1.0/install.sh | bash
+   If you are on Arch but `yay` is missing, do NOT try to bootstrap yay — fall
+   through to branch (d) and tell me you did so.
+
+3. RUN THE CHOSEN INSTALL COMMAND.
+   Execute exactly the one command for the branch you selected. STOP and report
+   the full command output if it exits non-zero. Do not silently retry with a
+   different channel.
+
+4. VERIFY.
+   Run `hive --version`. It must print a version string (expected: 0.1.0).
+   - If the command is not found, PATH may not yet include the install location.
+     Report the directory the channel installs into and the exact PATH line I
+     would need to add — but DO NOT edit any rc file yourself. Then STOP.
+   - If it errors for any other reason, STOP and report the output.
+
+5. OFFER `hive init`.
+   Ask me (do not assume yes) whether to run `hive init` in the current
+   directory to attach Hive to this project. Only run it if I say yes. If I
+   decline, tell me I can run `hive init .` later.
+
+6. SKILLS (capability-gated — only if a real marketplace exists).
+   The hive *skills* package is a SEPARATE repo installed through your agent's
+   plugin marketplace. It is NEVER installed by the core `hive` binary and NEVER
+   by copy-paste of skill files.
+   - Claude Code: if you can add a plugin marketplace (the "add marketplace" /
+     plugin-marketplace mechanism), OFFER to add the hive skills marketplace,
+     pointing at the marketplace manifest under `packaging/skills` (the future
+     `hive-skills` repo). Only add it if I say yes.
+   - Codex / Pi: only offer this if you actually expose an equivalent
+     marketplace mechanism. If you are not sure it exists, treat it as absent.
+   - If you have no marketplace capability, SKIP this step and say so explicitly:
+     "No plugin-marketplace capability detected; skipping the hive skills step."
+
+Stop conditions (halt and report; do not work around them):
+  - The install command in step 3 exits non-zero.
+  - `hive --version` in step 4 is not found or does not print a version.
+  - The selected channel's prerequisite is missing (e.g. Arch branch but no
+    `yay`) — fall through per step 2 and say so, or STOP if no branch applies.
+  - Any step would modify a shell rc file — surface the change and let me apply it.
+  - I decline `hive init` or the skills step — record it and stop pushing.
+
+When done, report: the OS/arch you detected, the channel you used, the installed
+version from `hive --version`, whether `hive init` ran, and whether the skills
+marketplace was added or skipped (and why).
+```
+
+## What this installs
+
+- The `hive` **binary** only. Channels, in priority order per host:
+  1. Homebrew on macOS or Linuxbrew — `brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive`
+  2. AUR on Arch — `yay -S hive-bin`
+  3. The bash one-liner fallback — `curl -fsSL https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/download/v0.1.0/install.sh | bash`
+- The **skills** package is deliberately out of scope for the binary install. It
+  lives in a separate `hive-skills` repo and is added through each agent's plugin
+  marketplace. See [`packaging/skills/README.md`](packaging/skills/README.md).
+
+After install, verify with `hive --version`, then `hive init .` in a project to
+attach Hive and `hive tui` to open the dashboard.
