@@ -0,0 +1,43 @@
+# Homebrew packaging
+
+`hive.rb` in this directory is the **source of truth** for the Homebrew formula.
+
+## Installing
+
+```sh
+brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive
+```
+
+This taps `ivankuznetsov/homebrew-hive` and installs the formula in one step.
+It is equivalent to:
+
+```sh
+brew tap ivankuznetsov/hive
+brew install hive
+```
+
+## Tap repo structure
+
+The tap lives at `github.com/ivankuznetsov/homebrew-hive`. Homebrew expects
+formulae under a `Formula/` directory:
+
+```
+homebrew-hive/
+  Formula/
+    hive.rb
+```
+
+## Release flow
+
+On release, automation copies `packaging/homebrew/hive.rb` from this repo into
+`Formula/hive.rb` in the tap repo, and replaces each
+`REPLACE_WITH_SHA256_AT_RELEASE` placeholder with the real SHA-256 from the
+release's `SHA256SUMS` file. Do not edit the tap copy by hand — change this
+file and let the release sync it.
+
+## Notes
+
+- The release artifacts are relocatable, self-contained app-directory tarballs
+  that bundle their own Ruby, so the formula declares **no** `ruby` dependency.
+- Runtime tools (`git`, `gh`, `jq`, `claude`) are surfaced in `caveats`, not as
+  hard `depends_on` entries.
