@@ -0,0 +1,70 @@
+# hive skills package
+
+Source of truth for the **separate `hive-skills` repo**. The contents of this
+directory are what that repo will hold; they live here in the core repo during
+v1 so the skill and its marketplace manifests can be developed alongside the CLI.
+
+> **The skills package is NOT installed by the core `hive` binary.** Installing
+> `hive` (Homebrew, AUR, or the `install.sh` one-liner — see the repo-root
+> `install.md`) puts only the `hive` CLI on your PATH. Skills are added
+> separately, through your coding agent's own **plugin marketplace**, and never
+> by copy-pasting skill files into place.
+
+## Layout
+
+```
+packaging/skills/
+├── .claude-plugin/
+│   └── marketplace.json                 # Claude Code marketplace manifest (name: hive)
+├── plugins/
+│   └── hive-workflow/
+│       ├── .claude-plugin/
+│       │   └── plugin.json              # plugin manifest
+│       └── skills/
+│           └── hive-workflow/
+│               └── SKILL.md             # the actual skill (agent-agnostic content)
+├── manifests/
+│   ├── codex.stub.json                  # STUB — format unconfirmed
+│   ├── pi.stub.json                     # STUB — format unconfirmed
+│   └── README.md
+└── README.md                            # this file
+```
+
+## Install in Claude Code (delivered end-to-end in v1)
+
+The Claude Code path is the one confirmed and delivered path. Add the hive
+marketplace, then install the `hive-workflow` plugin from it:
+
+1. Add the marketplace (points Claude Code at the `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json`
+   in the `hive-skills` repo — during development you can point it at this
+   `packaging/skills` directory):
+
+   - Interactively: run `/plugin`, choose **Add marketplace**, and give it the
+     repo (`ivankuznetsov/hive-skills`) or the local path to this directory.
+   - Non-interactively: `claude plugin marketplace add ivankuznetsov/hive-skills`
+     (or `claude plugin marketplace add ./packaging/skills` from the hive repo).
+
+2. Install the plugin:
+
+   - Interactively via `/plugin` -> **Browse plugins** -> `hive` -> `hive-workflow`.
+   - Non-interactively: `claude plugin install hive-workflow@hive`.
+
+The manifest declares a marketplace named `hive` with one plugin, `hive-workflow`,
+whose skill (`skills/hive-workflow/SKILL.md`) documents how to drive the hive
+pipeline (`hive new` / `status` / `brainstorm` / `plan` / `develop` / `open-pr` /
+`review` / `finalize` / `archive`, findings triage, and the human-only TUI).
+
+> **Assumption noted:** the exact `marketplace.json` schema (top-level `name`,
+> `owner`/`maintainers`, and a `plugins[]` array of `{name, source, description}`)
+> follows the standard Claude Code plugin-marketplace shape. If a field name
+> differs in your Claude Code version, prefer the shape your `claude plugin`
+> tooling validates.
+
+## Codex and Pi (UNCONFIRMED)
+
+Codex and Pi marketplace mechanisms are **not confirmed**. `manifests/codex.stub.json`
+and `manifests/pi.stub.json` are clearly-labelled placeholders — see
+`manifests/README.md`. Do not install skills into Codex or Pi by hand; wait for
+their marketplace mechanisms to be confirmed and for real manifests to replace
+the stubs. If an agent has no marketplace capability, the hive skills step is
+simply skipped (the repo-root `install.md` prompt handles that gate).
