@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@
+# Install acceptance scenarios (A–D)
+
+Reproducible run recipes for the four install-story acceptance scenarios
+from the plan. A and B are partly automatable in Docker; the brew path,
+macOS launchd, and the prompt-installer (C) are manual VM/host checklists;
+D is scriptable per channel.
+
+Pass criteria for every scenario: `hive --version` prints the release
+version, `hive doctor --deps` runs, and no system Ruby is required on the
+box for a packaged install.
+
+| Scenario | What it proves | Automation |
+|----------|----------------|------------|
+| A | `brew install ivankuznetsov/hive/hive` works on clean macOS arm64 | manual VM/host (`a-brew.sh` documents the steps) |
+| B | `yay -S hive-bin` + `yay -Syu hive-bin` upgrade on clean Arch | `b-aur.sh` (Docker/`makepkg`) |
+| C | `install.md` prompt installs via the right channel in an agent | manual (checklist in `c-prompt.md`) |
+| D | `hive uninstall` removes binary + service, preserves work | `d-uninstall.sh` (any channel) |
+
+Scripts exit non-zero on a failed assertion. They intentionally avoid
+`sudo` for the XDG one-liner path. Run them inside a throwaway
+container/VM — several mutate `~/.local`, `~/.config`, and package state.
+
+## Quick local smoke (no network, no package managers)
+
+`smoke-install-sh.sh` exercises `install.sh`'s OS/arch detection and the
+`hv` fallback branch against a fake release server, without downloading a
+real artifact. This is the only fully-hermetic, CI-friendly script here.
