+---
+title: hive update
+type: command
+source: lib/hive/commands/update.rb, lib/hive/install_channel.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [command, install, update, json]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: `hive update` upgrades hive through the install channel's **native updater** — it NEVER swaps the binary in place. It detects the channel via [[modules/service]]'s `Hive::InstallChannel.detect`, prints the exact command, and runs it for channels safe to run unattended (`brew`, `install_sh`); channels that need a user gate (`aur` helper, `dev` checkout) or `--dry-run` are printed only.
+
+## Usage
+
+```
+hive update [--dry-run] [--json]
+```
+
+## Behaviour by channel
+
+| Channel | Command | Runs it? |
+|---------|---------|----------|
+| `brew` | `brew upgrade ivankuznetsov/hive/hive` | yes (auto_updatable) |
+| `install_sh` | `curl -fsSL <install.sh URL> \| bash` | yes (auto_updatable) |
+| `aur` | `yay -Syu hive-bin` | **no** — printed (AUR helper may prompt / need sudo) |
+| `dev` | `git pull` | **no** — printed (update with git, not a package manager) |
+| `unknown` | none | prints a reinstall pointer |
+
+- `--dry-run` prints the command for **any** channel without running it.
+- Commands run through `bash -lc` so the `install_sh` pipeline works.
+- `--json` emits the `hive-update.v1` envelope.
+
+## JSON envelope (`hive-update.v1`)
+
+Success payload:
+
+```json
+{
+  "schema": "hive-update",
+  "schema_version": 1,
+  "ok": true,
+  "channel": "brew",
+  "command": "brew upgrade ivankuznetsov/hive/hive",
+  "executed": true,
+  "dry_run": false,
+  "auto_updatable": true,
+  "message": "hive update: ran `brew upgrade ...`"
+}
+```
+
+`channel` enum: `brew` / `aur` / `install_sh` / `dev` / `unknown`. `command` is `null` when no automatic path exists. `executed` is true only when hive actually ran it (auto_updatable channel, not `--dry-run`). The error payload carries `error_class` / `error_kind: "internal"` / `exit_code` (1 or 70). Contract in `schemas/hive-update.v1.json`.
+
+## Exit codes
+
+| Code | Meaning |
+|------|---------|
+| 0 | success |
+| 70 | internal error |
+
