 `HIVE_CLAUDE_BIN` env var overrides the `claude` binary, used by tests with `test/fixtures/fake-claude` and `fake-gh`.
 
+## Runtime preflight (`Hive::Preflight`)
+
+`lib/hive/preflight.rb` is the runtime-dependency checker. It reports which external tools hive shells out to are present, missing, or too old, with per-OS install hints. It **never installs anything** — these are runtime, not build-time, dependencies, so a missing tool does not block hive's own install. Surfaced via `hive doctor --deps`, the post-init preflight, and mirrored in shell for `install.sh`'s pre-Ruby phase (`packaging/lib/preflight.sh`).
+
+Checked tools (`Preflight::TOOLS`):
+
+| Tool | Required? | Version floor | Missing → status |
+|------|-----------|---------------|------------------|
+| `git` | yes | — | `missing` (blocking) |
+| `bash` | yes | — | `missing` (blocking) |
+| `claude` | no | `Hive::MIN_CLAUDE_VERSION` (2.1.118) | `warning`; present-but-old → `version_too_old` |
+| `gh` | no | — | `warning` |
+| `jq` | no | — | `warning` |
+
+`check` returns one result Hash per tool (`{ tool:, required:, found:, path:, version:, min:, ok:, hint: }`). `blocking?` is true when a required tool is absent OR a tool with a `min` is present-but-too-old; missing recommended tools warn but do not block. `current_os` buckets the host (`:macos` / `:arch` / `:fedora` / `:debian`) by probing for `pacman` / `dnf` / `rpm` to pick the right hint (e.g. `sudo pacman -S git` vs `sudo apt install git`). Version probes parse the first dotted-number token from `<tool> --version`.
+
+### `hive doctor --deps`
+
+`hive doctor --deps` opts the runtime-dependency rows into the doctor table / `hive-doctor.v1` envelope alongside the skill-check rows. The rows use `kind: "dependency"`, `agent: "runtime"`, and map preflight results to statuses: `present` (found + ok), `version_too_old` (found but below `min`), `missing` (required tool absent — fails the exit code), `warning` (recommended tool absent — non-fatal). Off by default so the skill-only surface and its row counts are unchanged. See [[commands/doctor]].
+
 ## Ruby version
 
 `Gemfile` declares `ruby "~> 3.4"`. `.rubocop.yml` pins `TargetRubyVersion: 3.4`. `Gemfile.lock` records 3.4.7 as the resolved version.
