+
+The idiomatic-install work (Homebrew tap, AUR `hive-bin`, `install.sh`,
+`install.md`, XDG paths, `hive update`/`uninstall`, daemon-as-service) landed
+with these deliberate boundaries — see [[commands/update]], [[commands/uninstall]],
+[[modules/service]], [[modules/paths]]:
+
+- **homebrew-core** submission deferred — tap-only for v1.
+- **`hive-git` AUR package** deferred — only the prebuilt `hive-bin` ships.
+- **Rolling/edge channel** and in-place `hive self-update` binary swap: not built (R6 — `hive update` always delegates to the native updater).
+- **Tier-3 platforms** (Alpine/musl, NixOS, BSD): excluded from the build matrix; tier-2 (macOS x86_64) is best-effort/allowed-to-fail.
+- **Single-file Tebako binary (R1/R2)** — UNRESOLVED. The primary artifact is a relocatable app-directory tarball because `bubbletea`/`lipgloss` are precompiled platform-specific Charm FFI gems (`Gemfile.lock`); a fused single binary must embed those `.so`/`.dylib` artifacts and a matching `arm64-darwin` precompiled gem must exist on RubyGems. Verify both before attempting a Tebako channel. Documented in `packaging/build/README.md`.
