diff --git a/wiki/modules/service.md b/wiki/modules/service.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..b6c54b92
--- /dev/null
+++ b/wiki/modules/service.md
@@ -0,0 +1,68 @@
+---
+title: Hive::Service + Hive::InstallChannel
+type: module
+source: lib/hive/service.rb, lib/hive/service/{base,launchd,systemd_user}.rb, lib/hive/install_channel.rb
+created: 2026-07-10
+updated: 2026-07-10
+tags: [service, daemon, install, launchd, systemd, architecture]
+---
+
+**TLDR**: `Hive::Service` registers the hive daemon loop as a login service — a **launchd** LaunchAgent on macOS or a **systemd --user** unit on Linux — wired to `hive daemon {start,stop,status}`. `Hive::InstallChannel.detect` classifies how this hive was installed (`brew` / `aur` / `install_sh` / `dev` / `unknown`) so `hive update` / `hive uninstall` drive the right native tooling instead of swapping files in place.
+
+## Hive::Service
+
+`Service.backend(platform:, runner:, binary_path:)` returns the platform-appropriate backend (`Launchd` on `:darwin`, `SystemdUser` on `:linux`; anything else raises `Hive::Error`). Every backend implements the same surface:
+
+| Method | Behaviour |
+|--------|-----------|
+| `register` | Write the unit file + `logs/` dir (idempotent), then run the post-write reload/bootstrap. Returns `unit_path`. |
+| `unregister` | Stop + remove the unit file. |
+| `enable` | Register + start now (launchctl bootstrap+kickstart / `systemctl --user enable --now`). |
+| `start` / `stop` | Lifecycle only, no file changes. |
+| `status` | `:active` / `:inactive` / `:not_installed`. |
+| `installed?` | The unit file exists on disk. |
+| `render` | The unit-file text (pure; no side effects). |
+
+Real `launchctl` / `systemctl` calls go through an injectable `runner` (default: `Open3.capture3`) so unit tests exercise rendering and dispatch without a live service manager.
+
+### Backends
+
+- **`Launchd`** — unit at `~/Library/LaunchAgents/dev.hive.daemon.plist` (`LABEL = "dev.hive.daemon"`). Driven by `launchctl bootstrap gui/<uid> <plist>` / `bootout` / `kickstart -k` / `print`. Template `packaging/service/dev.hive.daemon.plist.erb`.
+- **`SystemdUser`** — unit at `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/systemd/user/hive-daemon.service` (`SYSTEMD_UNIT = "hive-daemon"`). Driven by `systemctl --user {enable --now, start, stop, disable --now, is-active, daemon-reload}`. Template `packaging/service/hive-daemon.service.erb`.
+
+Both units are `Type=simple` / foreground (no `--detach`): the **service manager owns the lifecycle**, and the ExecStart runs `hive daemon start` with `HIVE_SERVICE_MANAGED=1` baked into the env so that in-process invocation runs the real loop instead of re-delegating. An explicit `HIVE_HOME` is propagated into the unit env so a service-managed daemon resolves the same home the operator used at `hive init`.
+
+### Helpers
+
+- `installed?(platform:)` — never raises on an unsupported platform (returns `false`), so callers keep the dev-checkout fork path as the default.
+- `resolved_binary` — the `hive` / `hv` launcher on PATH, else the running executable, baked into the unit's ExecStart.
+- `log_path` — `<Paths.state_home>/logs/daemon.log` (default `~/.local/state/hive/logs/daemon.log`); StandardOut/Err for launchd, foreground stdout for systemd.
+- `template(name)` — resolves `packaging/service/<name>` via `Paths.shared_asset` so installed artifact and dev checkout both find it.
+
+### Delegation from `hive daemon`
+
+`hive daemon {start,stop,status}` call `service_backend`: when a unit is installed (and `HIVE_SERVICE_MANAGED != 1`), lifecycle is delegated to the service manager (`svc.start` / `svc.stop` / `svc.status`) instead of the in-process PID-file fork. The service-invoked `start` (which carries `HIVE_SERVICE_MANAGED=1`) skips delegation and runs the foreground loop. Dev checkouts with no unit installed keep the fork path. See [[commands/daemon]] and [[operating]].
+
+## Hive::InstallChannel
+
+`InstallChannel.detect(binary_path:, runner:)` resolves the running launcher (following symlinks) and classifies it. It returns a `Detected` struct: `kind`, `binary_path`, `update_command`, `uninstall_command`, `auto_updatable`, `note`.
+
+| kind | Detected when | `update_command` | `uninstall_command` | `auto_updatable` |
+|------|---------------|------------------|---------------------|------------------|
+| `:brew` | launcher under `brew --prefix` | `brew upgrade ivankuznetsov/hive/hive` | `brew uninstall hive` | true |
+| `:aur` | `pacman -Qo <path>` names `hive-bin` | `yay -Syu hive-bin` | `sudo pacman -R hive-bin` | **false** (AUR helper may prompt / need sudo) |
+| `:install_sh` | launcher under `Paths.data_home` (`~/.local/share/hive`) | `curl -fsSL <install.sh URL> \| bash` | `hive uninstall` | true |
+| `:dev` | `bin/hive` inside a git checkout (sibling `.git` + `lib/hive.rb`) | `git pull` | `nil` | false |
+| `:unknown` | none of the above | `nil` | `nil` | false |
+
+Constants: `TAP = "ivankuznetsov/hive/hive"`, `AUR_PKG = "hive-bin"`, `INSTALL_SH_URL = "https://github.com/ivankuznetsov/hive/releases/latest/download/install.sh"`. `DEFAULT_RUNNER` shells out via `Open3.capture3` and is injectable for tests. Consumed by [[commands/update]] and [[commands/uninstall]].
+
+## Packaging
+
+Channel artifacts live under `packaging/{build,homebrew,aur,skills,service,lib}`, with `install.sh` and `install.md` at the repo root. The `bin/hive` launcher is dual-named: invoked as `hive` by default, or linked as `hv` by `install.sh` when a conflicting `hive` (e.g. Apache Hive) is already on PATH. Thor derives the program name from `$PROGRAM_NAME`, so `hv --help` renders `hv ...` with no extra wiring.
