 ## Autostart
 
+### Managed service (recommended — registered by `hive init`)
+
+`hive init` offers to register the daemon as a login service and enable+start it (see [[commands/init]] and [[modules/service]]). Once a unit is installed, `hive daemon {start,stop,status}` delegate to the service manager automatically — no separate `launchctl` / `systemctl` bookkeeping:
+
+- **macOS** — launchd LaunchAgent at `~/Library/LaunchAgents/dev.hive.daemon.plist` (label `dev.hive.daemon`).
+- **Linux** — systemd-user unit at `~/.config/systemd/user/hive-daemon.service`.
+
+Both run `hive daemon start` in the foreground (`Type=simple`) with `HIVE_SERVICE_MANAGED=1` in the unit env; the service manager is the supervisor. The service-managed log is `~/.local/state/hive/logs/daemon.log` (`hive daemon tail` follows it). To register/enable after the fact, re-run `hive init` on a TTY (or set `HIVE_REGISTER_SERVICE=1` for a non-interactive run). `hive uninstall` stops + deregisters the unit.
+
+The hand-installed sample units below remain valid for operators who want to customise the unit, or for the bot (which has no managed-service path yet).
+
